217. Contains Duplicate
AIM:Given an integer array nums, return true if any value appears at least twice in the array, and return false if every element is distinct.
Algorithm:
1.Start
2.Take the input array nums.
3.Sort the array in ascending order.
4.Traverse the sorted array from index 0 to n-2.
5.Compare the current element nums[i] with the next element nums[i+1].
6.If both elements are equal, return true because a duplicate exists.
7.If no adjacent elements are equal after the loop ends, return false.

CODE:class Solution {
public:
    bool containsDuplicate(vector<int>& nums) {
        sort(nums.begin(),nums.end());
        for(int i=0; i<nums.size()-1;i++)
        
            {
                if(nums[i]== nums[i+1])
                {
                    return true;
                }
            }  
            
            return false;

    }
};


