219. Contains Duplicate II

AIM:Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return true if there are two distinct indices i and j in the array such that nums[i] == nums[j] and abs(i - j) <= k.
Algorithm:
1.Start.
2.Create an empty unordered_map named mp.
3.Traverse the array nums from index 0 to n-1.
4.Check if the current element nums[i] is already present in the map using mp.find(nums[i]).
5.If the element is found, calculate the distance between the current index and the previous index:
        i - mp[nums[i]]
6.If the distance is less than or equal to k, return true.
7.Otherwise, store or update the current element and its index in the map:
        mp[nums[i]] = i;
8.Repeat Steps 4–7 for all elements in the array.
9.If no nearby duplicate is found after the loop ends, return false.
10.Stop.

CODE:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsNearbyDuplicate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int, int>mp;
        for(int i=0; i<nums.size(); i++)
        { 
           if(mp.find(nums[i]) != mp.end())
                {
                    if(i-mp[nums[i]]<=k)
                    {
                        return true;
                            
                    }
                }
                mp[nums[i]]=i;
    }
        return false;
    }
};
 

